    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1494"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1494">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/125a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Résumé of above correspondence re Benton.]</p>
                <p>Unofficially represent to Carranza the advisability of ordering Benton’s body
                    exhumed and delivered to relatives or Collector of Customs El Paso at once. The
                    body will furnish best possible proof <pb facs="0966" n="850" xml:id="pg_850"/>
                    of what occurred and a failure to deliver body is being used as basis for charge
                    that court martial was held after Benton’s death. We are doing everything in our
                    power to ascertain the facts and British Government is relying on us to do so.
                    Rush telegraphic reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
